fields.physical_description:
1. TINY TOWN TELEGRAPH OFFICE; panel of card printed in colours on pink to show the title, maker's marks, a child and animals in a field and two smaller illustration on the sides showing a train and a ship. The panel has two folds and the centre cut out to form a window. It is designed to stand up and acts as a serving counter.  The back surface is pink card.   9¼in x 6 7/8in folded (23.5x17.4cm)
2. tapper; varnished wooden block with two metal studs. There are two plugs with a wooden arm in the shape of a cross, also varnished, attached between them; this is supported by a small metal spring. Under the arm are metal screws which correspond with the studs on the block. 5½in x 2 7/8in (14x7.3cm)
3. TINY TOWN TELEGRAPH OFFICE; printed sheet of paper giving Morse Code and various call signs together with directions. It has also been stamped from the stamp block. 
4. TINY TOWN TELEGRAPH CO.; face mask; card printed in colours to show the top half of a face with a blue cap with black brim and the words printed in yellow. 
5. card block insert to which are attached by threads five groups of telegraphic equipment - CABLEGRAM; printed black on white paper; TINY TOWN TELEGRAPHS; printed black on white paper; TINY TOWN TELEGRAM; printed black on orange paper; THE WESTERN UNION TELEGRAPH COMPANY; printed black on cream paper; sets of blue and pink envelopes printed with THE TINY TOWN TELEGRAPH CO. All the parts are dirty. 
6. rubber stamp; black wood handle with stamp reading TINY TOWN TELEGRAPH CO. 
7. metal tin; which is rusty and will not open; printed on lid in black on the remains of gold is TINY TOWN POST JWS&S 
8-47. collection of disc; card covered on one side with red/pink paper printed in brown with a number from 1 to 6. 
8-11 1; 12-25 2; 26-29 3; 30-33 4; 34-38 5; 39-47 6 
48. box lid; card covered with dark red paper; on the lid is a label printed in colours to show the title and an illustration showing two children playing with the toy; at the bottom is Spear's trademark which has been partly stamped out with the addition of the stamp of Tom Smith's. On the reverse side is the name Telegraph and a list of cracker contents. 
49. box base; card covered with dark red paper; inside is divided into four compartments; one to house the tapper; another the card block; mask and instructions; one the stamp and tin and the fourth the card disc. Box and base are in poor and dirty condition.
fields.title: TINY TOWN TELEGRAPH OFFICE
fields.marks: J W Spear & Sons; London/ Made by JWS&S Bavaria
fields.history_note:
References: It was printed as part of the Spear Series in Bavaria, however, the marks on the lid have been inked over and the name TOM SMITH'S added. Inside lid is a typewritten label with No. 3166 Telegraph listing cracker contents.

Belonged to the donor; born 1915
fields.production_note:
Made by: Spear Series and Tom Smith's (crackers)
England/Germany
